						<summary>

						<p>Rock to the west of Kōdaṇḍarāmasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Parakēsarivarman Rājēndra (I) Year 4.</hi></p>						

						<p>This is very much damaged.</p>						

						<p>It records the endowment for a perpetual lamp to God Tiruvāḍāmalaiyāḻvār in Urōḍagam alias Pallavamalla-chaturvvēdimaṅgalam in Kaḷattūr-nāḍu in Kaḷattūr-kōṭṭam in Jayaṅgoṇḍachōḻa-maṇḍalam by Nāṭṭāṉ Kambaṉ-āḷi. He seems to have contributed sheep as also land for the purpose.</p>						

						</summary>
